@* MudBlazor provider island.

   WHY A SEPARATE COMPONENT WITH @rendermode HERE.
   MudBlazor's MudThemeProvider + MudPopoverProvider + MudDialogProvider +
   MudSnackbarProvider all require InteractiveServer context for theme
   variables to flow and popovers / dialogs / snackbars to mount.

   MainLayout itself CANNOT carry @rendermode (Body is a RenderFragment that
   can't be serialized across the rendermode boundary — see the full
   explanation in `Components/Routes.razor`). But a *child* component of a
   non-interactive layout CAN carry @rendermode, so this component sits
   inside MainLayout and acts as the single "everything interactive needs
   to mount below this line" anchor. Pages that opt into
   `@rendermode InteractiveServer` get their own circuit anyway, and
   non-interactive pages (Login, Register) keep working as static SSR
   because the providers themselves only matter for interactive fragments.

   Theme: <see cref="ServantSyncTheme.Build"/> maps MudTheme to the
   BRANDING.md color tokens — Primary=indigo (#3730a3), Secondary=violet,
   Tertiary=purple, Warning=amber, Error=rose, AppbarBackground=#1f1f2e. *@
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<MudThemeProvider Theme="_theme" />
<MudPopoverProvider />
<MudDialogProvider />
<MudSnackbarProvider />

@code {
    private readonly MudTheme _theme = ServantSyncTheme.Build();
}
